[3 bladen] [blad 1, recto] [Edouard de] Callatay, Cornelis Massys paysagiste, collaborateur de son père et de son frère et auteur de l'Album Errera, Bulletin Musées R. [= Bulletin Koninklijke Musea voor Schone Kunsten van België] XIV, 1965, p. 49ff. Here the landscape in the Hamburg Flora (by Jan Massys) which Tolnay, G.B.A. 1957, 73-80 attrib. partly to Bruegel, partly to Cornelis Massys given to Cornelis Massys; [blad 2, recto] F.G. Cornelis Massys & the Destruction of Sodom (Fischer, Lucerne) The landscape drawings assembled by Zwollo as she says herself, very different in mood, but the panoramic river [onleesbaar] with rocks (arco naturale) and with small houses on the right also in the River Landscape in Boymans (her figure 13) and the formation of the rocks related in landscape with Castle, Göttingen, University Coll., her figure 10. (both are attributions). The Berlin landscape drawing with Lot & Daughters does not show destruction of Sodom, but the 3 figures are in front of rocks and there is some distant relationship with the Lucerne figures. (The Dresden drawing of the 3 figures completely different); [blad 3, recto] An Zwollo, De landschaptekeningen van Cornelis Massys, in: Nederlands Kunsthistorisch Jaarboek 16, 1965, pp. 43-65, citaten pp. 60, 61 n. 27, 62 n. 28, 63.
